               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18790915-name-713" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18790915-name-713" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18790915-name-713" type="surname" value="MORGAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18790915-name-713" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM MORGAN</persName>
                  </hi>. My father is a grocer, of 67, Cornhill Road, Lambeth—on 31st July, about 3 p.m., I served the prisoner with a penny bottle of ginger-beer—he gave me a florin, I gave him 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 11<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. change—he drank it and went out—I put the florin in the till; there were no others there—a few minutes afterwards he came in again for a pennyworth of cake, and gave me another florin—I put it in the till and gave him 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 11<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. change, and he went away—I afterwards showed the two florins to my mother and took them to the baker's shop opposite to test them, and gave them back to my mother—about a week afterwards I saw the prisoner by the coke ovens—I Had known him before, and knew where be used to live—I am sure he is the man.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
